\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces  (A) The inner plate of model\nobreakspace {}\ref  {sec:model-basic} represents population-wide variation of exclusion state \(\theta _{ig}\) within any given gene \(g\) whereas the outer plate genome-wide variation. (B) Within gene variation disappears in the limit \(\nu \rightarrow 0\), which simplifies model structure to\nobreakspace {}\ref  {sec:model-basic-nu-0}. (C) On the other hand when \(\nu \rightarrow \infty \) within gene variation is maximized, which leads to another simplified structure that is\nobreakspace {}\ref  {sec:model-basic-nu-infinit}. Note that only the exclusion state \(\theta _{ig}\) and its ``dependency ancestors'' are shown; \(\kappa , \phi _{ig}, \psi _v,...\) are connected to \(\phi _{ig}\) as in Figure \ref  {fig:plate-local}. }}{8}{figure.3}}
\newlabel{fig:plate-basic}{{3}{8}{(A) The inner plate of model~\ref {sec:model-basic} represents population-wide variation of exclusion state \(\theta _{ig}\) within any given gene \(g\) whereas the outer plate genome-wide variation. (B) Within gene variation disappears in the limit \(\nu \rightarrow 0\), which simplifies model structure to~\ref {sec:model-basic-nu-0}. (C) On the other hand when \(\nu \rightarrow \infty \) within gene variation is maximized, which leads to another simplified structure that is~\ref {sec:model-basic-nu-infinit}. Note that only the exclusion state \(\theta _{ig}\) and its ``dependency ancestors'' are shown; \(\kappa , \phi _{ig}, \psi _v,...\) are connected to \(\phi _{ig}\) as in Figure \ref {fig:plate-local}}{figure.3}{}}
